      <body>-1 This ticket should be closed as the file path for this patch doesn't exist and def ask is now in the following path:
Thor::Shell::Basic in the basic.rb file.

It appears that $stdin.gets has been applied already in master branch.

Here is the code snippet:

@@@ ruby
      # Ask something to the user and receives a response.
      #
      # ==== Example
      # ask(&quot;What is your name?&quot;)
      #
      def ask(statement, color=nil)
        say(&quot;#{statement} &quot;, color)
        $stdin.gets.strip
      end
@@@</body>
